{"entityMap":{},"blocks":[{"key":"c7ne9","text":"On 4th May, Richard Thake was re-elected. He represents Knebworth at the County Council. He also represents Codicote, St Pauls Walden, Kimpton, Wymondley and St Ippolyts. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e79to","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"74o9k","text":"Residents are often confused about the difference between the two councils. County runs many more things, including social care, children's services (including schools) and most of the roads. To put things into context, the District Council has a budget of less than one percent of that of the county. Per capita spending by the County is more than thirteen times that of the District.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":302,"length":10,"style":"ITALIC"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9oi6f","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2vk8a","text":"One of the primary functions of the District Council is to be the Planning Authority. This does not have such a big budgetary impact, but it does have an impact on people's lives. This is the reason I write about it so often in these columns. I wrote last month about the vote to allow the Draft Local Plan to forward for examination by the Planning Inspector. Development of a Local Plan, which is a set of policies, with which all developments must comply, is part of Planning Policy. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":470,"length":15,"style":"ITALIC"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7nc1a","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e960d","text":"Planning Control is a separate function. Its function is to examine planning applications to ensure that they follow all the policies. The policies are rules found not only in the Local Plan but also in the National Planning Policy Framework. Inevitably, there is scope for developer and objector to disagree on the interpretation of the wording of policies. To allow some degree of arbitration the Planning Control Committee examines more contentious applications. If the developer does not agree with the decision of the Committee, it can appeal to the Planning Inspectorate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":16,"style":"ITALIC"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9qmh7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e16b6","text":"Objectors have been successful in blocking, or causing major modifications of a number of applications. Applications for solar farms on two Green Belt sites were refused or abandoned. Applications for development of two sites in Park Lane were scaled back, including the recent application on the site of the former Hamilton Billiards company. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bs3gq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bl10b","text":"If the current Draft Local Plan is adopted, and the Green Belt boundary is moved, no development will take place without a full planning application. The new policies on access, parking, affordable housing etc. will all apply. The edge-of-village sites include a figure for the number of dwellings these might accommodate, but these are notional figures derived from a pro-forma assumed density. The do not in any way imply that the Planning Control Committee will actually grant permission for this number of houses to be built.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b3fni","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctupi","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}]}